OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FUndercover policing tactics
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fnot justified - report     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The use of undercover policing tactics 
OL,6, from the 1960s onwards was not         
OL,7, justified and the unit should have been
OL,8, disbanded early on, a report says.     
OL,10,FEx-senior judge Sir John Mitting said  
OL,11,Fmost groups infiltrated by the Special 
OL,12,FDemonstration Squad posed no threat.   
OL,14,FHis report for the Undercover Policing 
OL,15,FInquiry details tactics such as forming
OL,16,Fsexual relationships and using the     
OL,17,Fnames of dead children for cover.      
OL,19,FThe end did not justify the means, the 
OL,20,Freport concludes.                      
